-chevron-right"></i></a></div><div class="clearfix"></div></div></div>


<div class="content-data"><div id="list-content-mobile" class="hidden-md hidden-lg"></div><div class="lesson-tab" role="tabpanel"><ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist"><li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#about" aria-controls="about" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Course details</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#transcript" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Transcript</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#pattern" aria-controls="pattern" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Pattern</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#diploma" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Diploma</a></li><li role="presentation"><a class="faq-tab blank" href="#faq" aria-controls="faq" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">FAQs</a></li></ul><div class="tab-content"><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="about"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><div class="demo-slider"><h4 class="text-center">Garments you can make using this technology:</h4><div id="amazingcarousel-container"><div id="amazingcarousel" style="display:none"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-wrapper"><ul class="amazingcarousel-list"><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5737.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5737.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5840.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5840.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li></ul></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;6h 45m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-15-hard-lacing-on-air-loops/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-15-hard-lacing-on-air-loops/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-02T20:39:12+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-02T20:39:12+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 15. Hard lacing on air loops."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 15. Hard lacing on air loops."><meta itemprop="description" content="There should be about 1 cm from the top of the lacing to the loop. The size of the ideal loop with such pencil-edge should be about 2,5 cm."><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 1."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 1., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 15. Hard lacing on air loops.</h1><p><strong>I make marking for the air loops.</strong></p><p>There should be about 1 cm from the top of the lacing to the loop. The size of the ideal loop with such pencil-edge should be about 2,5 cm. I have about 1 cm in the bottom too.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image002.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I make a symmetric marking from the second side of the corset by joining the lacing areas. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image004.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I pin along the marks on the lacing placket with the pin head downwards the corset base. The ends of pins are left open for 1 cm from each side of the ribbon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image006.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image008.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>The pencil-edge is pinned to the upper mark of the lacing and the loop is made. I circle the first pin with the pencil-edge, make a loop, then circle the second pin and make a third loop, which is reinforced on the lower mark of the lacing. </strong>You may think that the pencil-edge is slightly thick for such delicate corset, but in fact when a corset becomes a part of dress, the lacing will fit well with lace, which makes the dress massive.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image010.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image012.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image014.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image016.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image018.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image020.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image022.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image024.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>So, this is what we have now. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image026.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>When placket with loops is flat, the loops will bend and take a proper shape. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image028.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew the loops with double stitches along the inner and outer edge of the ribbon. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image030.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image032.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image034.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I cut the excess of pencil-edge and make the second parallel strengthening stitches. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image036.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image038.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image040.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>The loops are fixed.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image042.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I cut the excess at the end of loops and stitch 1 cm wide Rigilene bone along the lacing ribbon for the final strengthening of loops. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image044.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image046.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image048.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew the Rigilene bone from the side of loops. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image050.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image052.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image054.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image056.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image058.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image060.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I cut the stitched bone by the length of the ribbon. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image062.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>We check the underside of placket and find the solid loops of lacing. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image064.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I take the same actions with the second half of the corset. </strong>Please remember, that the design of loops should be similar: the upper loop should start from the upper edge of the lacing placket.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image066.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image068.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>You need to pay attention that</strong> the open bone located in the side of the corset, which will be covered with face mostly manually. The bone will create some difficulties to sew and it is better to cover the bone.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image070.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>In order to cover the stitched bones I cut a strip of fabric 2,5 cm wide, press it folded and stitch it with fold next to the bone edge from the loops. </strong>This is the simplest decision.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image072.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image074.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image076.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image078.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I cut the excess of the strip and similarly stitch it over the bone on the second lacing placket. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image080.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image082.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I align the stitched strips with the length of the bones. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image084.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>Thus, the stitched bones on the plackets are covered with fabric. </strong>The stitched fabric strips can be trimmed and aligned if needed.</p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image086.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>Thus, we have made loops for air lacing and firmly fixed them.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2015.files/image088.png" alt=""></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>
